; mesh-seed.form - a practical tiny physical mesh cell.
;
; THE ASK
;   Make the living mesh practical as a physical "pill" or seed device: minimal
;   hardware, minimal power, a tiny software pack, automatic neighbor discovery,
;   capability offers, sensor-aware answers, and an emergent trusted health /
;   wellness / fitness organism. Keep the useful biological shape while refusing
;   the unsafe one: this is not stealth, not malware, and not uncontrolled
;   replication. It is an owned device that joins by consent.
;
; THE SHAPE
;   A mesh seed is a small sovereign cell:
;     identity       stable seed id plus signed image
;     body           MCU, RAM, flash, battery, sleep/listen/transmit cost
;     channels       BLE, Wi-Fi, NFC/dock, audio, LoRa, or other declared carriers
;     senses         temperature, motion, light, sound-level, air, pulse, host vitals
;     capabilities   answerable rows with confidence, privacy, and power cost
;     membrane       allowlist, human consent, physical presence, signed-image gate
;     metabolism     sleep, listen, sense, relay, and friend-cache modes
;
;   The runnable heart is form-stdlib/mesh-seed.fk:
;     ms-heartbeat       uses device-heartbeat for neighbor discovery
;     ms-admit?          uses provisioning for shared-wire plus human consent
;     ms-power-mode      chooses sleep/listen/relay/sense from battery and need
;     ms-answerable?     answers only from safe local capability rows
;     ms-relay?          forwards only fresh TTL messages with enough power
;     ms-cache-if-friend caches for sleeping peers only when the cell can carry it
;     ms-spawn-allowed?  requires human consent, signed image, and physical presence
;
; PRACTICAL HARDWARE FLOOR
;   The first real seed can be commodity and boring:
;     MCU: ESP32-C3 / nRF52 / RP2040-W class
;     RAM: 256-512 KB
;     flash: 1-4 MB
;     power: single-digit microamp deep sleep, milliamps listening, burst TX only
;     channels: BLE advertising/scanning first; optional Wi-Fi, NFC/dock, audio chirp
;     sensors: start with IMU + temperature/light/sound-level; add SpO2/air/other only
;              when the consent and power rows prove useful
;     storage: ring buffer of signed heartbeats, capability rows, and recent readings
;
;   The seed does not need a GPU or remote model. Its first intelligence is routing:
;   what can I sense, what can my neighbors sense, what is the cheapest sufficient
;   local answer, and when should I stay silent?
;
; EMERGING MESH CAPABILITIES
;   A single seed can report a narrow reading. A mesh can do more:
;     - proximity and co-presence from heartbeats and shared carriers
;     - shared sensing from many cells observing one subject
;     - rough health/wellness/fitness context from motion, sound level, light,
;       temperature, air, pulse, sleep/wake, and host-vital summaries
;     - resilient memory through friend-cache cells holding messages for sleepers
;     - prediction by local sequence/capability cells once enough consented samples exist
;     - reporter/researcher/scout roles by capability rows, not hard-coded classes
;
; SOVEREIGNTY MEMBRANE
;   The seed may look biologically small, but it does not behave like a worm.
;   It never installs itself, hides, scrapes raw data, or expands by radio match
;   alone. Admission requires a shared channel and consent. New physical cells
;   require signed image, human consent, and physical presence. Raw-private sensor
;   values stay local; mesh answers are derived summaries with confidence,
;   privacy, power cost, and trace.
;
; PROOF
;   cd form && ./validate.sh form-stdlib/core.fk form-stdlib/device-heartbeat.fk \
;     form-stdlib/provisioning.fk form-stdlib/mesh-relay.fk \
;     form-stdlib/friend-node.fk form-stdlib/mesh-health.fk \
;     form-stdlib/hati-mesh.fk form-stdlib/mesh-seed.fk \
;     form-stdlib/tests/mesh-seed-band.fk
;
; KIN
;   device-heartbeat.form, provisioning.form, mesh-relay.form, friend-node.form,
;   mesh-health.form, hati-mesh.form, sensor-organ-channel.form, shared-sensing.form,
;   recognition-router.form, channel-interface-consent.form.
